{
  "stem": "19550.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But everybody tried to take some winter clothing along, because if, well, we're going to be evacuated east, east is cold, you know.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And of course, people tried to stuff in as much food as they could lay their hands on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Everybody had different ideas of what was advisable.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It's--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you know, people began to pour out of these-- the homes in the ghetto where they were onto this [?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Star ?] Street.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And by that time, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the sentry were more directly under the control of the, of the gendarmes, because they never came inside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They, so to say, ruled through the Jewish Council and by guarding the perimeter.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But here they began to drive us with considerable brutality.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] my sister has-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and my sister Izabella has actually described it in, in her book.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were being squeezed into a line.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This is-- I never in my life want to hear the word 'five in a row,' because that seemed to have been fixed in the minds of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had to line up five to a row.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were shoving and pushing and shouting.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And, and total disarray, of course, and chaos, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] because, you know, the lame and the hurt and the, and the dumb and the, and the blind.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they couldn't be told to keep order and to stay in line, then they would lash out at them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And apparently, this young SS man had a [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] whip, and he lashed out with a whip at my mother.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--I was-- what?",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
